  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen factors are fully assessed; the Equivalency of input parameters factor is recorded as not-assessed on the basis that the assessor judged it inapplicable to the COU—however the correct encoding for that determination would be factorStatus 'not-applicable', not 'not-assessed'. At MRL 3 this omission materially weakens package credibility (W-EP-04).",
