      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that this factor does not apply to the present COU because the CFD model and the validation experiment share identical nominal input parameters by design—the pump geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions were specified to match. Consequently, no formal equivalency assessment was conducted and the factor was left unassessed. Note: the technically correct encoding for a factor judged inapplicable would be factorStatus 'not-applicable'; the use of 'not-assessed' here is the latent weakener at MRL 3."
